The '''78th Primetime Emmy Awards''' will honor the best in American [[prime time]] television programming from June 1, 2025, until May 31, 2026, as chosen by the [[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]].<ref name="Rules and Procedures">{{cite web |url=https://www.televisionacademy.com/files/assets/Downloads/2026-rules-procedures-v2a.pdf |title=78th Emmy Awards – 2025–2026 Rules and Procedures |publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] |access-date=March 3, 2026}}</ref> The awards ceremony will be held live on September 14, 2026, at the [[Peacock Theater]] in [[Downtown Los Angeles]], California, and will be preceded by the 78th Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards on September 5 and 6. The ceremony will be produced by Jesse Collins Entertainment and broadcast in the United States by [[NBC]] and [[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]].<ref name="Airdate">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2025/11/2026-emmys-airdate-nbc-1236621428/ |title=2026 Emmys Gets Airdate on NBC |last=Petski |first=Denise |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=November 18, 2025 |access-date=March 3, 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbc.com/nbc-insider/2026-emmys-air-date-announcement |title=NBC Reveals the Air Date for the 78th Emmy Awards in 2026 |last=Phelan |first=Chris |publisher=[[NBC]] |date=November 18, 2025 |access-date=March 3, 2026}}</ref><ref name="Calendar">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2025/tv/news/emmy-calendar-2026-voting-nomination-dates-tv-academy-1236607719/ |title=TV Academy Reveals Emmy Calendar for 2026 — Including Eligibility, Submission, Voting and Nomination Dates |last=Schneider |first=Michael |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=December 12, 2025 |access-date=March 3, 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2026/04/jesse-collins-entertainment-emmys-2-1236876445/ |title=Jesse Collins Entertainment to Produce Emmys, Again |last=White |first=Peter |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=April 30, 2026 |access-date=May 1, 2026}}</ref> [[Mariska Hargitay]] will host the event.<ref name="Hargitay"/>

