==Ceremony information==
[[File:Mariska Hargitay Woodstock Film Festival.jpg|right|thumb|upright|alt=Mariska Hargitay in 2025.|[[Mariska Hargitay]] will host the ceremony.]]

The nominations for the 78th Primetime Emmy Awards will be announced on July 8, 2026, at the Television Academy's Wolf Theatre in [[North Hollywood, Los Angeles]], hosted by actor [[Jeff Hiller]] and actress [[Liza Colón-Zayas]], along with Television Academy chair [[Cris Abrego]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.televisionacademy.com/features/news/awards-news/260618-emmy-nominations-announcement |title=Emmy Winners Liza Colón-Zayas and Jeff Hiller to Announce 78th Emmy Awards Nominations July 8 |publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] |date=June 18, 2026 |access-date=June 18, 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/watch-2026-emmy-nominations-livestream-online-1236640358/ |title=2026 Emmy Nominations: Watch the Livestream |last=Jeffries |first=Naomi |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 8, 2026 |access-date=July 8, 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/lists/emmy-nominations-full-list-nominees-scorecard/ |title=Emmy Nominations 2026 List |last1=Gomez |first1=Dessi |last2=Hipes |first2=Patrick |last3=Pedersen |first3=Erik |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 8, 2026 |access-date=July 8, 2026}}</ref> Unlike previous years, nominations for two categories were announced three hours early—[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Reality Competition Program|Outstanding Reality Competition Program]] and [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Variety Series|Outstanding Variety Series]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2026/07/colbert-kimmel-john-oliver-jon-stewart-snl-late-night-emmys-1236975168/ |title=Stephen Colbert, Jimmy Kimmel, John Oliver, Jon Stewart & 'SNL' to Battle It Out for Bumper Late-Night Emmy or Emmys |last=White |first=Peter |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 8, 2026 |access-date=July 8, 2026}}</ref> the latter revived this year following the announcement that [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Scripted Variety Series|Outstanding Scripted Variety Series]] and [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Talk Series|Outstanding Talk Series]] would be merged.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.televisionacademy.com/features/news/awards-news/260128-emmys-variety-rules |title=Emmys Rules Merge Variety Categories |publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] |date=January 28, 2026 |access-date=July 8, 2026}}</ref> On July 7, actress [[Mariska Hargitay]] was announced as the ceremony's host.<ref name="Hargitay">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2026/07/mariska-hargitay-host-2026-emmy-awards-nbc-1236975778/ |title=Mariska Hargitay to Host 2026 Emmy Awards on NBC |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 7, 2026 |access-date=July 7, 2026}}</ref> [[NBC]] and the [[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences|Television Academy]] considered talent both within and outside of [[NBCUniversal]] for the job, but ultimately hired NBC's ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''{{'}}s lead actress since the network is celebrating its 100th anniversary. This will be the first time since the [[Angela Lansbury]]-[[45th Primetime Emmy Awards|hosted 1993 ceremony]] that the event will not be emceed by a comedian, comedy performer, or TV personality/reality host.<ref name="Hargitay"/>

As usual, to avoid a conflict with the network's broadcast of ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football]]'', the event was scheduled to a Monday night, instead of a Sunday, since it is NBC's turn to air the awards ceremony.<ref name="Airdate"/>

This year, the Television Academy will present a new major award (a first in nearly 20 years) with the creation of the Legacy Award, which will be presented annually to television programs that have made a "profound and lasting impact" on audiences, and remain relevant to culture, society and the industry.<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.televisionacademy.com/features/news/awards-news/2026-legacy-award-260108 |title=Television Academy Announces Plans for First New Major Award in Nearly 20 Years |publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] |date=January 8, 2026 |access-date=March 3, 2026}}</ref>

Jesse Collins, Dionne Harmon, and Jeannae Rouzan-Clay of Jesse Collins Entertainment will serve as executive producers of the telecast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.televisionacademy.com/features/news/awards-news/260707-78th-emmys-host-mariska-hargitay |title=Mariska Hargitay to Host 78th Emmy Awards on NBC |publisher=[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] |date=July 7, 2026 |access-date=July 7, 2026}}</ref>

